node.text:
8 dev sites you didn’t know existed

Video by @allthecode

teamsuccess.io/UX - Catch common usability problems before user testing

learnxinyminutes.com - Every language you can imagine, search and learn

slazzer.com/api - An AI powered API to remove backgrounds from images

crontab.cronhub.io - A tool to workout out cron syntax, so you con’t have to

namae.dev - Check all the nooks and crannies of the web for that new name you want to use

flaticon.com - Icons, lots and lots of icons also look at (materialdesignicons.com nom package)

regex101.com - Regular expression tester with syntax highlighting, explanation, cheat sheet

explainshell.com - Paste in a shell command and get an explanation of what it is

See how many you can use in your next project, save for later 😀
